    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-29T04:04:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-29T04:04:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/4–352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East (<persName corresp="#p_RGMB1"
                            type="from">Ridgway</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>operational immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-04-29T18:04:00+09:00"
                            >April 29, 1952—6:04 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>CX 67738. Re C 67178.<note n="1" xml:id="d108fn1">Dated Apr. 19, <ref
                            target="#pg_160">p. 160</ref>.</note> Available data on Opn <gloss
                        target="#t_SCATTER1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scatter</hi>
                    </gloss> as of 28 Apr is shown below: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Total number screened to return to Communist control: <gloss
                                target="#t_NK1">NK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 25492, <gloss target="#t_SK1"
                                >SK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 4240, <gloss target="#t_CCF1"
                                >CCF</gloss> 5202, <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> 3657, total
                            38591.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>The total number of unscreened <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss>
                            and <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> in compounds where screening has
                            not been initiated: <gloss target="#t_NK1">NK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 39471, <gloss target="#t_SK1"
                                >SK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 263, <gloss target="#t_CCF1"
                                >CCF</gloss> 1147, <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> 6449, total
                            47330.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Results to date of rescreening those who initially were screened and
                            elected to remain in the <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> custody: <list>
                                <item>Col A. Initially screened to remain with <gloss
                                        target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>; <gloss target="#t_NK1"
                                        >NK</gloss> 31369, <gloss target="#t_SK1">SK</gloss> 11602,
                                        <gloss target="#t_CCF1">CCF</gloss> 14487, CI 26120, total
                                    83578.</item>
                                <item>Col B. Number of those Col A rescreened; <gloss
                                        target="#t_NK1">NK</gloss> 29179, <gloss target="#t_SK1"
                                        >SK</gloss> 10987, <gloss target="#t_CCF1">CCF</gloss>
                                    14127, CI 21059, total 75352.</item>
                                <item>Col C. Total number remaining in <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                        >UNC</gloss> custody after rescreening; <gloss
                                        target="#t_NK1">NK</gloss> 29062, <gloss target="#t_SK1"
                                        >SK</gloss> 10906, <gloss target="#t_CCF1">CCF</gloss>
                                    13712, CI 20919, total 74599.</item>
                                <item>Col D. Total number who reversed decision and are to return to
                                    Communists; <gloss target="#t_NK1">NK</gloss> 117, <gloss
                                        target="#t_SK1">SK</gloss> 81, <gloss target="#t_CCF1"
                                        >CCF</gloss> 415, CI 140, total 753.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Shipment from Koje-Do of those who will be retained in <gloss
                                target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> custody after rescreening: <gloss
                                target="#t_NK1">NK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 19045, <gloss target="#t_SK1"
                                >SK</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 9043, <gloss target="#t_CCF1"
                                >CCF</gloss> 10712, <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> 15974, total
                            54774.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
